summary: This FBI 302 report documents a consent search of Alfredo Rodriguez's vehicle and personal cell phones on November 4, 2009. The search resulted in the seizure of an AT&T Sony Ericsson cellular telephone from his vehicle and the examination of an iPhone he was carrying.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Individual who provided consent to search his vehicle and personal cell phones, resulting in the seizure of a cellular telephone.

events.title: Consent search of Rodriguez's vehicle and phones
events.description: Pursuant to consent provided by Alfredo Rodriguez, FBI agents searched his tan Chevrolet Trailblazer and seized an AT&T Sony Ericsson cellular telephone. They also searched an iPhone he was carrying.

keyFacts: Alfredo Rodriguez consented to a search of his vehicle and personal cell phones on November 4, 2009.
An AT&T Sony Ericsson cellular telephone was seized from his tan Chevrolet Trailblazer during the search.
Rodriguez also consented to the search of an iPhone he was carrying on his person.
The original FD-26 Consent to Search Form signed by Rodriguez was placed in the case file.
